description.plain:
Dennis Princewell Stehr, better known as Mr Probz, is a Dutch singer, rapper, actor and musician. His song “Waves” became his first international hit, after being remixed by Robin Schulz in 2014.

Mr Probz started his career, creating Dutch songs like “Meisje luister” with Kleine Viezerik and “Sukkel voor de liefde” with The Opposites.

In 2013 he released his debut album The Treatment for free through SoundCloud. The album peaked to number 12 on the Dutch Albums Chart.

Since then, he has released the singes “Waves,” as above mentioned, “Nothing Really Matters,” “Fine Ass Mess,” and “Till You’re Loved.”

description.plain:
Dutch rapper/singer Mr. Probz dropped a new track called “Waves” while he was still working hard on his first debut album, The Treatment.

At first, this track was meant to be just a little preview/teaser for the album, but it blew up unexpectedly.
